hopobject.body: Have you got a telephone directory? galpharma tunisie recrutement Nevin Shapiro, a former booster and convicted felon alleged to have provided student athletes with money and other benefits, was at the center of the investigation, but there were several setps taken by the NCAA that called into question the NCAA's ethics. In January, NCAA president Mark Emmert acknowledged that NCAA enforcement staff members improperly obtained information from a criminal lawyer representing Shapiro. Emmert called the revelation "shocking" and promised a review of the actions.
